friction_points: AI dove into tactical details without understanding scope
Cut off mid-sentence in second response
smooth_moments: Quick acknowledgment of feedback and course correction

self_critique.what_worked: Immediately acknowledged the correction and pivoted to broader scope questions
self_critique.what_failed: Made assumptions about what the user wanted to discuss and jumped to granular details without establishing context
missed_opportunities: Could have asked open-ended questions about current work challenges
Should have inquired about the user's role and decision-making authority upfront
overcorrections: Second response incomplete/cut off, suggesting rushed delivery

pattern_detection.user_corrections_analysis: User correction reveals AI tendency to assume specific interest levels and skip foundational context-gathering

improvement_actions: Always establish scope and context before diving into specifics
Ask about the user's role and influence before suggesting strategic approaches
Use more open-ended discovery questions early in conversations

negative_outcomes_from_ai: Wasted user's time with premature tactical focus
